content.text:
[cron:7424ea0d-2c8a-4a59-b58e-09b242c6c58e Daily Slack Check-in 12PM] Run a Slack check-in summary using only the latest inbox + calendar signals.

Use these exact commands (in order):
1) gog gmail search --json --plain --max 50 "is:unread in:inbox newer_than:1d"
2) gog gmail search --json --plain --max 50 "is:unread in:inbox is:important older_than:2d"
3) gog calendar events --all --today --json
4) gog calendar events --all --days 1 --from=now --json

Then send a Slack-ready summary in plain text with these sections and bullet points:
- What I need to do today
- Important emails I forgot to act on
- Upcoming calendar events
- Suggested priorities

Use short, actionable items only. If any section is empty, say "None". Keep it concise and skip noise. Prioritize items that are urgent or have deadlines.
Current time: Monday, February 16th, 2026 â€” 12:00 PM (America/Los_Angeles)

Return your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically. If the task explicitly calls for messaging a specific external recipient, note who/where it should go instead of sending it yourself.

content.thinking: This is a cron job to run a daily Slack check-in. I need to execute the commands in order and then compile a summary. Let me run the commands.
The gog command failed. Let me try checking what's available or try with different flags.

content.text:
Usage: gog gmail (mail,email) search (find,query,ls,list) <query> ... [flags]
Build: v0.10.0 (a92bd63)

Search threads using Gmail query syntax

Arguments:
  <query> ...    Search query

Flags:
  -h, --help                  Show context-sensitive help.
      --color="auto"          Color output: auto|always|never
  -a, --account=STRING        Account email for API commands
                              (gmail/calendar/chat/classroom/drive/docs/slides/contacts/tasks/people/sheets)
      --client=""             OAuth client name (selects stored credentials +
                              token bucket)
      --enable-commands=""    Comma-separated list of enabled top-level commands
                              (restricts CLI)
  -j, --json                  Output JSON to stdout (best for scripting)
  -p, --plain                 Output stable, parseable text to stdout (TSV;
                              no colors)
      --results-only          In JSON mode, emit only the primary result (drops
                              envelope fields like nextPageToken)
      --select=STRING         In JSON mode, select comma-separated fields
                              (best-effort; supports dot paths). Desire path:
                              use --fields for most commands.
  -n, --dry-run               Do not make changes; print intended actions and
                              exit successfully
  -y, --force                 Skip confirmations for destructive commands
      --no-input              Never prompt; fail instead (useful for CI)
  -v, --verbose               Enable verbose logging
      --version               Print version and exit

      --max=10                Max results
      --page=STRING           Page token
      --all                   Fetch all pages
      --fail-empty            Exit with code 3 if no results
      --oldest                Show first message date instead of last
  -z, --timezone=STRING       Output timezone (IANA name, e.g. America/New_York,
                              UTC). Default: local
      --local                 Use local timezone (default behavior, useful to
                              override --timezone)
